  "_readme": "Dynamic multi-DEX, multi-asset, multi-hop route scanner config. Copy to routes.config.json. Addresses cross-checked against BscScan and each protocol's own docs/source (see ../keeper/addresses.bsc.json and ../keeper/tokenlist.bsc.json for full source list) - not pulled from memory. wrappedNative must be whitelisted as an asset AND have a Chainlink price feed set on-chain (setPriceFeed) for gas-cost-in-asset accounting to work; same for every baseAsset you want gas-aware filtering on. intermediateTokens has 58 real tokens (from PancakeSwap's own official token-list repo) - that alone yields far more than 200 candidate pairs via the token-graph x router-registry approach in routes.ts. THENA is deliberately NOT included: its V3 AMM (Algebra Integral, dynamic fees) isn't interface-compatible with the Uniswap-V3-style quoter already implemented, and its legacy V2-style router address couldn't be independently cross-verified with the same confidence as the routers below - see ARBITRAGE-UPGRADE.md.",
